<subpara id="RM000000PDW01AX_02" type-id="64" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___000079B00000">
<name>MONITOR DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>The ECM optimizes the valve timing using the VVT system to control the intake camshaft. The VVT system includes the ECM, the OCV and the VVT controller. The ECM sends a target duty-cycle control signal to the OCV. This control signal regulates the oil pressure supplied to the VVT controller. The VVT controller can advance or retard the intake camshaft.</ptxt>
<ptxt>After the ECM sends the target duty-cycle control signal to the OCV, the ECM monitors the OCV current to establish an actual duty-cycle. The ECM determines the existence of a malfunction and sets the DTC when the actual duty-cycle ratio varies from the target duty-cycle ratio.</ptxt>
</content5>
</subpara>
